# Preview Demo I18n

- New registry UI components must land as a synchronized set: `registry/default/<name>/<name>.tsx`, a `registry.json` `registry:ui` item, `src/pages/components/<name>/index.tsx`, component demos, `src/router/routes.ts`, regenerated API docs, and preview i18n entries.
- Any component development work, including adding, changing, renaming, or removing registry components or preview demos, must update the preview i18n dictionaries in the same change.
- Component preview pages should use the standard `PreviewDemoPage` shape: `import.meta.glob` for modules and raw sources, explicit `DEMO_PATHS`, `getPreviewDemoExamples`, `sourceRoot`, and `trailing={<PreviewApiTable api={apiDocs.<name>} />}`.
- Demo files should export `meta satisfies PreviewDemoMeta` as the default export and a named `Demo` component.
- When adding or changing component demos, make every user-visible demo string translatable through the preview i18n layer.
- Add missing English-to-Chinese preview strings in `src/i18n/preview/index.tsx` for demo titles, descriptions, labels, button text, table captions, statuses, and helper copy.
- When new registry component TSDoc appears in `src/generated/preview-api-docs.json`, add matching Chinese API doc entries in `src/i18n/preview/api-docs.zh.ts`.
- Keep code identifiers, prop names, paths, and literal type examples untranslated.
- After updating registry component docs, run `pnpm run build:api` before checking translations so new API doc keys are visible.
- After changing `registry.json` or registry source, run `pnpm run build:registry` so `public/r/*.json` stays aligned with the preview.
